  "text": "Although the disparate effects of the lpr mutation in EAE in the different mouse strains may be due to the particular immunizing neuroantigens that were used (MOG35-55 and guinea pig MBP versus PLP139-151 in our studies), as well as the use of pertussis toxin (not used in our experiments), it is probable that the main reason for the apparent disparate outcomes between our findings and the results reported by others is the genetic differences in the strains of mice used, i.e., B10.PL (H-2 u ) and B6 (H-2 b ) versus SJL(H-2 s ). Indeed, it has been reported that multiple background genes influence the incidence and severity of lymphoaccumulation and histopathologic manifestations of systemic autoimmunity in mice homozygous for the lpr mutation [CITATION_1] . SJL mice are highly autoimmune-prone mice and redundant apoptotic-initiating stimuli, i.e., TNF/TNF-receptor-mediated apoptosis and/or nonapoptotic mechanisms of tissue destruction, may play the major effector role in CNS demyelination in this mouse strain.",
